<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n09119h"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n09" href="#n09119h">N09 (VI.B.1)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n09all.htm#n09119h"> 119(h)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> Joseph 2<sup>nd</sup> wife</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">That St. Jude the Apostle was the brother of Jesus Christ] was at first understood in the most obvious sense, and it was supposed that the brothers of Jesus were the lawful issue of Joseph and Mary. A devout respect for the virginity of the mother of God suggested to the Gnostics, and afterwards to the orthodox Greeks, the expedient of <mark>bestowing a second wife on Joseph</mark>. <small> Edward Gibbon, <a name="EGDF2" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#EGDF2"><cite title="source">Decline and Fall of the Roman Empire</cite></a> (ed. unknown) 238n (Chapter XVI)</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
